<br>
Group was me, cleric, and another magican. No slows, and the pet did not die, and the mobs did.<br>
<br>
Low down time actually (considering the group make up), as we all had KEI, and the cleric was level 54. He healed the pets, we nuked. Mob dead, We pulled.<br>
<br>
We killed at a pretty good rate, just went as we got him flagged to show him the zone for an hour (as it was late). We had no problems at all.<br>
<br>
Actually been in a lot of groups where they say we need a slower, but if we have a cleric, and my pet, the pet has never once said. WE CAN'T DO THIS, we need a slower. Instead it wades into battle, and victory follows shortly after.<br>
<br>
All the clerics/shaman/druids I group with love my pet, and heal it without being asked. They know the damage it deals and respect it, and don't want it to end so they heal ole Goner.<br>
<br>
Two cases in point. A cleric said do you have the 61 water pet? Its awesome (I corrected her, said it was level 62. Yes I did have it, but as no slower will use Air for the stuns. She readily agreed good idea).<br>
<br>
Second case made me feel so good about playing a magician. I joined a group, and after a few kills she sent a tell. Said to me, do you know how much damage you do?<br>
<br>
I said yes, but was confused, than she added. With you in the group our kill times dropped by 30 seconds. I was amazed (I replaced a level 57 Paladin), and while I think 30 seconds is very hard to believe, it did feel good, and I had no idea that the damage I added was that noticeable. I guess I can relate that to the fact my only high level character is my 65 Magician, and I am use to that kill rate.<br>
<br>
It feels good to know your damage is seen by others, and respected. She made a another comment that I feel really shows up this fact.<br>
<br>
She added, I guess all those that quit their to make a rogue or a monk after Luclin came out may go back to their magician again.<br>
<br>
